The paper discusses auto-encoder variants and their ability to capture the local manifold structure of the unknown data generating density. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of auto-encoders in image processing (cs.CV) and their ability to estimate local moments, which suggests that it may also belong to the computer vision sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Markov Chain Monte Carlo (MCMC) methods (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT) in the context of auto-encoders, which further supports the likelihood of these sub-categories.
